37:59.364 --> 38:01.714
♪ Leave a damsel for Delilah ♪

38:03.890 --> 38:06.719
♪ Dagger for the damned,
the damned, the damned ♪

38:08.938 --> 38:12.202
♪ Fine wine and foie gras ♪

38:12.333 --> 38:14.292
♪ In my view ♪

38:14.422 --> 38:16.859
♪ Nothing's ever given away ♪

38:16.990 --> 38:21.124
♪ I believe to advance
then you must pay ♪

38:22.822 --> 38:24.084
♪ In my view... ♪

38:24.214 --> 38:25.346
what you doing?

38:25.477 --> 38:27.130
Just looking at some old pics.

38:28.741 --> 38:29.437
Who's that?

38:30.743 --> 38:32.919
That's my father.

38:33.049 --> 38:34.486
Your grandfather.

38:34.616 --> 38:38.577
My grandfather?
What's he like?

38:38.707 --> 38:42.058
He was tough on me.

38:42.189 --> 38:44.626
But he was only trying to
prepare me for the world.

38:44.757 --> 38:47.063
Because responsibilities
take no days off?

38:47.194 --> 38:49.501
Yeah.

38:49.631 --> 38:51.459
He taught me that.

38:51.590 --> 38:53.896
Well, what else
did he teach you?

38:54.941 --> 38:56.725
Well, for one,

38:56.856 --> 38:59.162
he was a cop, like me.

38:59.293 --> 39:00.816
♪ Say no more ♪

39:00.947 --> 39:02.340
♪ Animal, you're no longer
vicious ♪

39:02.470 --> 39:04.690
♪ Say no more, please ♪

39:04.820 --> 39:08.041
♪ Just cradle, cradle ♪

39:08.171 --> 39:10.304
♪ You're no longer vicious ♪

39:12.567 --> 39:16.310
♪ Say no more, please, baby ♪

39:16.441 --> 39:18.138
♪ Just cradle, cradle ♪

39:18.268 --> 39:20.662
♪ In my view ♪

39:20.793 --> 39:22.185
♪ Nothing's ever given away ♪

39:22.316 --> 39:23.926
♪ Damned, the damned,
the damned ♪

39:24.057 --> 39:26.973
♪ I believe to advance
then you must pay ♪

39:27.103 --> 39:28.627
♪ Say no more, please ♪

39:28.757 --> 39:32.195
♪ In my view,
love will never come my way ♪

39:32.326 --> 39:33.675
♪ Animal, rest in peace ♪

39:33.806 --> 39:35.111
♪ So when I leave ♪

39:35.242 --> 39:37.200
♪ You'll be dancing
on my grave ♪

39:37.331 --> 39:38.941
♪ You'll be
dancing on my grave. ♪

39:39.072 --> 39:40.639
Here you are, still
making me meet you

39:40.769 --> 39:42.380
in the middle of nowhere.

39:44.643 --> 39:47.297
Just so I can talk
and you can not listen.

39:54.348 --> 39:56.089
I miss you, Bishop.

40:03.401 --> 40:05.272
Figured I'd see you again, Fisk.

40:09.363 --> 40:12.584
You are Colton Fisk,

40:12.714 --> 40:14.063
aren't you?

40:16.065 --> 40:18.938
And you're everything
Bishop always said you were.

40:19.068 --> 40:21.680
- When'd you know?
- I had my suspicions.

40:23.159 --> 40:24.073
The way you moved.

40:24.204 --> 40:27.512
The way you handled your weapon.

40:27.642 --> 40:28.948
Reminded me of Bishop.

40:31.211 --> 40:33.953
- He did train you, didn't he?
- He did.

40:34.083 --> 40:37.696
What I don't understand is...

40:39.872 --> 40:42.265
...why the prisoner act?

40:42.396 --> 40:43.963
Just to flush out a mole?

40:44.093 --> 40:46.487
I knew posing a serious
threat to the Brigada

40:46.618 --> 40:49.403
Would force their inside man
to contact them.

40:49.534 --> 40:51.536
Why go through all of that?

40:51.666 --> 40:54.321
Why put all of our lives
in danger?

40:54.452 --> 40:55.931
You could have called
the CIA tac team

40:56.062 --> 40:57.280
anytime you wanted.

40:57.411 --> 40:59.413
How far were you willing
to play this out?

40:59.544 --> 41:01.894
As far as it took
to get answers.

41:02.024 --> 41:03.896
You must've known about Griffin.

41:04.026 --> 41:05.506
It was you who
put him on the team.

41:06.551 --> 41:08.988
But there was someone else
I was worried about.

41:10.685 --> 41:11.556
Me?

41:14.341 --> 41:16.691
- You thought I was a mole?
- You and Griffin

41:16.822 --> 41:18.780
worked closely together
on a number of things.

41:18.911 --> 41:20.347
I needed to find out.

41:20.478 --> 41:21.740
And?

41:23.611 --> 41:25.961
I knew you were clean
when you didn't kill Griffin.

41:26.092 --> 41:29.443
If he would have exposed me,

41:29.574 --> 41:31.619
I would have
had to silence him.

41:31.750 --> 41:33.447
I'm glad you understand.

41:33.578 --> 41:35.449
I understand the logic.

41:35.580 --> 41:37.190
Doesn't mean I agree with it.

41:37.320 --> 41:40.019
You don't have to.

41:40.149 --> 41:42.500
You just have to answer
the phone when I call.

41:42.630 --> 41:44.023
Your arrangement
with the Agency,

41:44.153 --> 41:46.678
the one Bishop negotiated
for you-- it's under

41:46.808 --> 41:48.593
my supervision now.
You work for me.

41:48.723 --> 41:51.900
First of all,
I don't work for anyone.

41:52.031 --> 41:55.904
Especially not someone
as reckless as you.

41:56.035 --> 41:58.777
Your little playacting
got two good agents killed.

41:58.907 --> 42:01.214
Sanford and Shaw
were as guilty as Griffin.

42:01.344 --> 42:03.042
They were as dirty.
Not Brigada moles,

42:03.172 --> 42:05.653
but they'd sold out their
country to other bad actors.

42:05.784 --> 42:09.178
Truth is,
everyone on that team

42:09.309 --> 42:11.137
was guilty of something.

42:11.267 --> 42:12.660
You put my life in danger.

42:13.792 --> 42:15.010
What was I guilty of?

42:15.141 --> 42:17.186
Of getting Bishop killed.

42:17.317 --> 42:19.580
He never should have
been on that plane.

42:19.711 --> 42:22.540
He was supposed to be looking
into something for me that day.

42:22.670 --> 42:24.846
Instead he disregarded
his own safety

42:24.977 --> 42:26.805
in a reckless pursuit
of Mason Quinn,

42:26.935 --> 42:28.546
all because of you

42:28.676 --> 42:31.070
and your selfish obsession.

42:32.462 --> 42:34.290
If not for you, McCall...

42:35.553 --> 42:37.685
Bishop is still alive today.

